cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "zero: an open-source AlphaEvolve-style evolutionary algorithm discovery engine"
abstract: >
  zero is an open-source clone of DeepMind's AlphaEvolve (April 2025). It pairs a
  population-based island-model evolutionary search with an LLM-driven mutation
  operator that proposes new candidate programs each generation. zero ships with
  three problem evaluators (sortnet8, matmul44_z2, capset) and reproduces several
  published baselines.
